## ðŸ“‚ Project Structure & Conventions

This project follows the **ITCSS architecture** for organizing styles and the **BEM methology** for naming clases.

<details>
<summary>ITCSS (Inverted Triangle CSS)</summary>

Styles are orgnised using ITCSS (Inverted Triangle CSS) method.
This splits styles into layers, going from generic to specific.

![inverted triangle](./assets/pics/it.png)  

- **Settings** â€“ variables, colors, fonts

- **Tools** â€“ mixins, functions

- **Generic** â€“ resets, normalize

- **Elements** â€“ base HTML elements (h1, p, a)

- **Objects** â€“ layout patterns (.o-page, .o-grid)

- **Components** â€“ UI blocks (.c-tabs, .c-section)

- **Utilities** â€“ helpers (.u-hidden, .u-text-center)

This layered structure avoids conflicts and keeps code scalable.

ðŸ“– dive in: [ITCSS Explained](https://www.xfive.co/blog/itcss-scalable-maintainable-css-architecture)
</details>
<details>
<summary> BEM (Block Element Modifier)
</summary>
Classes are named using the BEM convention

- **Block** â†’  sandalone entity (.tab-panel)
- **Element** â†’ part of block (.tabs__tab)
- **Mofifier** â†’ variation od blocck/element (.tabs__tab--active) 

ðŸ“– dive in: [BEM methology](https://getbem.com/introduction/):

</details>

<details>
<summary> Combining ITCSS & BEM</summary>
To keep things clear, use prefixes:

- o â†’ Objects (o-page,o-container)
- c â†’ Components( c-section,c-tabs)
- u â†’ Utilities (u-hidden)

It can sometimes get confusing,what goes where...
</details>